title: Bonavista Foods Inc. Recalls Pork Products Produced Without Benefit Of Import Inspection
summary: WASHINGTON, Dec. 18, 2015 Bonavista Foods Inc., Ovid, N.Y. establishment, is recalling approximately 4,338 pounds of cured pork products that were not presented at the U.S. point of entry for inspection, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.
